issue_body:
Currently all the pixel types, like rgb_pixel, have 8-bits per color channel, except for grayscale.
It would make sense to have each type have a larger range as more and more images are available with wider color gamuts. Most newer cameras also have a 16-bit per channel output.

I am willing to add the changes, but I think I need some guidance.

Here is what I have so far (compiles but untested).



Each pixel structure will only accept unsigned types for the color channels. Also made backwards compatible. [modifications]:
```
    template <typename T = uint8, typename std::enable_if<std::is_unsigned<T>::value, T>::type = false>
    struct rgb_pixel_t
    {
        /*!
            WHAT THIS OBJECT REPRESENTS
                This is a simple struct that represents an RGB colored graphical pixel.
        !*/
        typedef T type;

        rgb_pixel_t (
        ) {}

        rgb_pixel_t (
            T red_,
            T green_,
            T blue_
        ) : red(red_), green(green_), blue(blue_) {}

        T red;
        T green;
        T blue;
    };
    typedef rgb_pixel_t<> rgb_pixel;
```

Aliases to be used for code cleanup [new]:
```
    template <typename P>
    using is_pixel_t = typename std::integral_constant<bool, std::is_same<P, rgb_pixel>::value
                                   || std::is_same<P, bgr_pixel>::value
                                   || std::is_same<P, rgb_alpha_pixel>::value
                                   || std::is_same<P, hsi_pixel>::value
                                   || std::is_same<P, lab_pixel>::value>;
    template <typename P>
    using is_grayscale_t = typename std::integral_constant<bool, std::is_same<P, unsigned char>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, unsigned short>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, unsigned int>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, unsigned long>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, char>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, signed char>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, short>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, int>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, long>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, int64>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, uint64>::value>;
    template <typename P>
    using is_float_grayscale_t = typename std::integral_constant<bool, std::is_same<P, float>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, double>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, long double>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, std::complex<float>>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, std::complex<double>>::value
                                                             || std::is_same<P, std::complex<long double>>::value>;
```

Helper specializations [new]:
```
    template <typename P, bool S>
    struct eval_if_type_t;
    template <typename P>
    struct eval_if_type_t<P, false>
    {
        using type = P;
    };
    template <typename P>
    struct eval_if_type_t<P, true>
    {
        using type = typename P::type;
    };
    template <typename P>
    using select_type_t = typename eval_if_type_t<P, is_pixel_t<P>::value>::type;

    template <typename P, bool S>
    struct select_min_t;
    template <typename T>
    struct select_min_t<T, false>
    {
        static T min() { return std::numeric_limits<T>::min();}
    };
    template <typename T>
    struct select_min_t<T, true>
    {
        static T min() { return -std::numeric_limits<T>::max();}//float
    };
    template <typename P>
    using select_float_t = class select_min_t<P, std::is_floating_point<P>::value>;
```

The bulk of the changes move the separate specializations for the pixel_traits structure, along with the grayscale counterparts, into a single location (will be condensed using the aliases)  [replacements]:
```
    template <typename P, typename E>
    struct pixel_traits;
...
    template <typename P, typename E = typename std::enable_if<std::is_same<P, rgb_pixel>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, bgr_pixel>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, rgb_alpha_pixel>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, hsi_pixel>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, lab_pixel>::value

                                                  || std::is_same<P, unsigned char>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, unsigned short>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, unsigned int>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, unsigned long>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, char>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, signed char>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, short>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, int>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, long>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, int64>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, uint64>::value

                                                  || std::is_same<P, float>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, double>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, long double>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, std::complex<float>>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, std::complex<double>>::value
                                                  || std::is_same<P, std::complex<long double>>::value
            , P>::type>
    struct pixel_traits
    {
        constexpr static bool rgb  = std::is_same<P, rgb_pixel>::value || std::is_same<P, bgr_pixel>::value;
        constexpr static bool rgb_alpha  = std::is_same<P, rgb_alpha_pixel>::value;
        constexpr static bool grayscale = !(std::is_same<P, rgb_pixel>::value
                                          || std::is_same<P, bgr_pixel>::value
                                          || std::is_same<P, rgb_alpha_pixel>::value
                                          || std::is_same<P, hsi_pixel>::value
                                          || std::is_same<P, lab_pixel>::value);
        constexpr static bool hsi = std::is_same<P, hsi_pixel>::value;
        constexpr static bool lab = std::is_same<P, lab_pixel>::value;
        enum { num = rgb_alpha ? 4 : (grayscale ? 1 : 3) };
        //constexpr static long num = rgb_alpha ? 4 : (grayscale ? 1 : 3);
        typedef select_type_t<P> basic_pixel_type;
        //static basic_pixel_type min() { return (1<<((sizeof(basic_pixel_type)*CHAR_BIT)-1));}
        //static basic_pixel_type max() { return ~(1<<((sizeof(basic_pixel_type)*CHAR_BIT)-1));}
        static basic_pixel_type min() { return select_float_t<basic_pixel_type>::min();}
        static basic_pixel_type max() { return std::numeric_limits<basic_pixel_type>::max();}
        constexpr static bool is_unsigned = std::is_unsigned<basic_pixel_type>::value;
        constexpr static bool has_alpha = std::is_same<P, rgb_alpha_pixel>::value;
        inline basic_pixel_type get_pixel_intensity (const P& src);
    };
```

Backwards compatibility for grayscale [replacements]:
```
    template <typename T>
    using grayscale_pixel_traits = class pixel_traits<T>;

    template <typename T>
    using float_grayscale_pixel_traits = class pixel_traits<T>;
```

It is obviously not finish, but if this is a direction dlib can go then I will continue working on it.

A list of maps, such as the minimal test case below, should be parsed successfully, however an error occurs when attempting to parse such a structure with PyHCL.

sampleinput.tf:
```
resource = [{
    foo = [{
        bar = {}
    }]
}]
```
Output (PyHCL 0.3.6):
`
ValueError: Line 1, column 12: unexpected LEFTBRACE
`

This issue was [reported and fixed](https://github.com/hashicorp/terraform/issues/7142) for the golang parser last year. Test case [assign_deep.hcl](https://github.com/hashicorp/hcl/blob/master/test-fixtures/assign_deep.hcl) tests this structure, and for the golang parser this snippet is marked as [valid](https://github.com/hashicorp/hcl/blob/master/decoder_test.go#L230). The same test case exists for PyHCL, however the [same snippet](https://github.com/virtuald/pyhcl/blob/master/tests/lex-fixtures/assign_deep.hcl) is marked as [invalid](https://github.com/virtuald/pyhcl/blob/master/tests/test_parser.py#L49), meaning the test case appears to pass.

Test script:

```
#!/usr/bin/env python
import crython
import time

@crython.job(second='*/3')
def foo():
    print("I'm using */3 syntax.")

@crython.job(second=range(0, 60, 2))
def bla():
    print("I'm using range(0, 60, 2).")

if __name__ == '__main__':
    crython.start()
    try:
        while True:
            time.sleep(0.2)
    except KeyboardInterrupt:
        pass

    print("Done")
```

Prints:
```
I'm using range(0, 60, 2).
I'm using range(0, 60, 2).
I'm using range(0, 60, 2).
... etc ...
```

I would expect "`I'm using */3 syntax.`" to be printed every three seconds also, but it's not.

Is this a bug or am I doing something wrong ?

