I am trying to use python-pptx to generate pptx file from python 3.3.2 Embedded in C++ application .
It is working fine for first time and crashes when i try to import  "pptx" for next time.
Here is my code

```
void TestPPTX()
{
std::string code = 
"from pptx import Presentation\n\
prs = Presentation();\n\
prs.save(\"sss.pptx\");\n\
del sys.modules[\"pptx\"];\n\
";	
	Py_InitializeEx(0);
	PyRun_SimpleString(code.c_str());
	Py_Finalize();
	return;
}

void main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
	TestPPTX(); // Works correctly
	TestPPTX();	// crashes
	getch();    
}

```

When i move the Py_Finalize(); to main function it works 

```
void TestPPTX()
{
std::string code = 
"from pptx import Presentation\n\
prs = Presentation();\n\
prs.save(\"sss.pptx\");\n\
del sys.modules[\"pptx\"];\n\
";
	Py_InitializeEx(0);
	PyRun_SimpleString(code.c_str());
	return;
}


void main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
	TestPPTX(); // Works correctly
	TestPPTX();	// Works correctly
	Py_Finalize();
	getch();    
}
```

I want to know any memory leak is there in pptx and how to sort out this issue.

thanks
Srinivas

