@jaraco, @takluyver has proposed that we elevate the `entry_points.txt` file format to being a PyPA interoperability specification, rather than being an internal implementation detail of `setuptools`: https://github.com/pypa/python-packaging-user-guide/pull/390

I'm inclined to say yes, since it will better allow new publishing tools like `flit` to declare plugins for existing applications that use `pkg_resources` for plugin management, and also allow new projects like `entrypoints` to experiment with alternate approaches to reading and caching the runtime lookup entry point metadata, without risking any compatibility breaks for current `pkg_resources` users.

However, I'd like to get an explicit +1 from you before we go ahead and do that. The main consequence is that if you later decided you wanted to change the entry points file format, that would now have to go through the PEP process, rather than being a purely internal setuptools design discussion.

